Data Cleaning Project (Most Important)
This is the closest to real data engineering work.
Scenario
A data file contains invalid values.
data = [100,250,None,400,"NA",500,700.5,"",900,"Missing",150]
Requirements
Create
Valid numeric values
Invalid values
Numbers greater than 300
Numbers multiplied by 2
Numbers rounded (where applicable)
Data type of every element
Count:
Valid values
Invalid values
Integers
Floats
Strings

Finally calculate

Sum
Average
Maximum
Minimum

using only the valid numeric values.
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

data = [100,250,None,400,"NA",500,700.5,"",900,"Missing",150]
valid_numeric_values = [x for x in data if type(x) is int or type(x) is float]
print(f"Valid numeric values are {valid_numeric_values}")
invalid_values = [x for x in data if type(x) is not int and type(x) is not float]
print(f"Invalid values are {invalid_values}")
num_abv_300 = [y for y in valid_numeric_values if y >300]
print(f"Numbers greater than 300 are {num_abv_300}")
twice_num = [2*y for y in valid_numeric_values]
print(f"Twice of the given number are {twice_num}")
datatype_list = ["integer" if type(x) is int
else "float" if type(x) is float
else "string" if type(x) is str
else "None" for x in data]
print(datatype_list)
print(f"Number of valid values are {len(valid_numeric_values)}")
print(f"Number of invalid values are {len(invalid_values)}")
print(f"Count of integer values are {datatype_list.count('integer')}")
print(f"Count of float values are {datatype_list.count('float')}")
print(f"Count of string values are {datatype_list.count('string')}")
print(f"Sum of values is {sum(valid_numeric_values)}")
print(f"Average of values is {(round(sum(valid_numeric_values)/len(valid_numeric_values),2))}")
print(f"Largest Value of all valid values is {max(valid_numeric_values)}")
print(f"Smallest Value of all valid values is {min(valid_numeric_values)}")
